# Statistical rationale

The package uses the upstream raw `pvalue` column and recalculates
adjusted p-values within local hierarchy families rather than relying on
the incoming global `p.adjust`. At the visible starting level, all
visible root terms are corrected together. At deeper levels, direct
visible siblings under the same canonical parent are corrected together.

This approach is appropriate when the intended interpretation is
explicitly branch-aware rather than one fully flat ranking across the
entire ontology.

